<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> close one’s eyes • close your eyes and think of England</xh5><p> <i>close one’s eyes</i>—(also: shut one’s eyes) pretend that one has no knowledge of smth.; ignore smth.: If the authorities choose to <u>close their eyes</u>, the only thing that will pry them open is public pressure.</p><p> <i>close your eyes and think of England</i>—(also: shut your eyes and think of England) a humorous advice to smb. faced with an unpleasant task <i>(originally a wedding-night advice for Victorian brides to succumb to unwanted sex):</i> Live large. Tip big. And when they bring the check, just <u>close your eyes and think of England</u>.</p> </entry>
